other_tests.findings: The gallbladder is distended, with multiple echogenic, shadowing stones. There is gallbladder wall thickening of up to 7 mm. The common bile duct is not dilated, measuring 6 mm. The liver is markedly diffusely echogenic, likely representing fatty liver disease. The right kidney measures 10.4 cm and demonstrates no stone, mass, hydronephrosis.
